			"created_at": "2026-02-02T16:04:43Z",
			"updated_at": "2026-02-02T17:10:28Z",
			"body": "Thank you for the pull request!\r\n\r\n> This change skips only the broken sections, logs a warning, and writes an IMPORT_ERROR.md file so failures remain visible while allowing the rest of the notebook to import.\r\n\r\nPrior to this change, a dialog box was shown that notified users of the failure (with a link to the Joplin Forum). With this change, is the dialog box still shown?\r\n\r\n> Fixes https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/issues/14211\r\n> Some OneNote .onepkg / .one files contain malformed pages (missing ink data or invalid XPS/PDF references) that currently cause the entire import to fail.\r\n\r\n#14211 might be a separate issue.\r\n\r\nThe incomplete `.onepkg` import bug seems to be a regression from https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/pull/14094. Prior to #14094, `.onepkg` files were extracted via `EXPAND.exe`. Each `.one` file within the `.onepkg` was processed separately, with [errors handled here](https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/blob/c278b45c7876953d39328b78db303b6845421d91/packages/lib/services/interop/InteropService_Importer_OneNote.ts#L99). With #14094, all sub-files within the `.onepkg` archive are processed by the Rust logic modified by this pull request.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/laurent22/joplin/issues/14211 is reported for v3.5.12, which doesn't include #14094.\r\n\r\n**Edit**: Corrected pull request link.",
