			"updated_at": "2026-02-02T17:24:09Z",
			"body": "> Prior to this change, a dialog box was shown that notified users of the failure (with a link to the Joplin Forum). With this change, is the dialog box still shown?\r\n\r\n@h-jangra I've opened https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/pull/14246 and marked you as a co-author! The main differences from this pull request are:\r\n- Sends errors back to JS for error handling.\r\n  - As a result, the \"Some files failed to import\" dialog box is shown.\r\n- Doesn't create an `IMPORT_ERROR.md` file.\r\n  - It could still make sense to create an `IMPORT_ERROR.md`. However, most import errors should already be reported in an \"Errors\" file (created by `section.rs`). Others are logged and handled by JS in `InteropService_Importer_OneNote`.\r\n\r\n",
